{"title":"All-New Alchemy Rogue Gravel & Argos Ti MTB join updated Arktos w/ flip chip","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/07/all-new-alchemy-rogue-gravel-argos-ti-mtb-join-updated-arktos-w-flip-chip/","date":1633618824000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191059/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike4-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191059/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike4-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191059/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191059/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191059/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191059/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike4.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-273845\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>It appears that Alchemy has been busy. Quite busy. This year at Sea Otter they’re unveiling two completely new bikes, a substantial update to an existing model, and even more options for custom frame finishes – including in-house Cerakote.</p><h2>Alchemy Argos Ti Hardtail</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191104/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191104/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike6.jpg\" alt=\"Alchemy Argos titanium hardtail\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191104/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike6.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191104/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191104/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike6-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191104/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191104/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike6-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Named after the Argos Trail which will be directly behind Alchemy’s soon-to-be headquarters in Golden, CO, the Argos is meant to be the perfect bike of choice for said trail. Using Alchemy’s own custom blended USA titanium, the frame is built to climb the Colorado Rockies without giving up much on the downhills.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193348/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-geometry.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193348/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-geometry.png\" alt=\"Alchemy Argos geometry\" width=\"922\" height=\"274\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193348/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-geometry.png 922w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193348/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-geometry-297x88.png 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193348/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-geometry-800x238.png 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193348/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-geometry-120x36.png 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193348/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-geometry-768x228.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 922px) 100vw, 922px\"></a></p><p>Calling it an ‘Aggressive, Trail-oriented geometry,” the <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=bc9bec8a-e945-427c-be5d-909db8f98199&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Falchemybikes.com%2Fproducts%2Fargos-hardtail-mountain-bike\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Argos Ti Hardtail</a> includes a 65º head tube angle and 75.5º seat tube angle, and offers clearance for up to 29 x 2.5″ tires.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191106/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191106/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike7.jpg\" alt=\"Argos headtube\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191106/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike7.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191106/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike7-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191106/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike7-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191106/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike7-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191106/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike7-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>A tapered head tube sits in front of internal cable routing ports, including routing for an internal dropper post.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191101/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191101/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike5.jpg\" alt=\"Argos titanium seat stay chain stay\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191101/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike5.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191101/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191101/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191101/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191101/Alchemy-Argos-Titanium-hard-tail-mountain-bike5-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>The frame uses Boost 148mm dropout spacing, a threaded bottom bracket shell, and cold-forged chain stays and seat stays.</p><p>Available with custom stack &amp; reach sizing, and various paint and build kit options, pricing starts at $3,999 for the frame only, and complete builds from <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=bc9bec8a-e945-427c-be5d-909db8f98199&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Falchemybikes.com%2Fproducts%2Fargos-hardtail-mountain-bike\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">$6,299-$8,299</a>.</p><p><strong>Pricing and Availability:</strong></p><p>● Frame (without Fox Factory 34 Fork) – $3,999</p><p>● Frame (with Fox Factory 34 Fork) – $4,499</p><p>● Builds ranging from $6,299 to $8,299</p><p>● Available immediately</p><h2>Alchemy Rogue Gravel Bike</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191122/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20215.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191122/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20215.jpg\" alt=\"Alchemy Rogue gravel bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"664\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191122/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20215.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191122/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20215-297x164.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191122/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20215-800x443.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191122/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20215-120x66.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191122/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20215-768x425.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Staying in the dirt, but a little bit faster, the <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=bc9bec8a-e945-427c-be5d-909db8f98199&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Falchemybikes.com%2Fproducts%2Frogue-gravel-bike\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">new Rogue</a> adds to the Alchemy stable. Standing alongside the existing Ronin, the new Rogue is a more capable gravel bike with a slacker head tube angle, more tire clearance, and some other nice touches. Like a SRAM Universal Derailleur Hanger. Apparently, it may be the first US-made gravel bike to include the SRAM UDH which should make it easier to find a replacement hanger in a pinch.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191129/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20218.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191129/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20218.jpg\" alt=\"Alchemy flat mount brakes\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191129/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20218.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191129/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20218-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191129/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20218-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191129/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20218-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191129/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20218-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Handmade in Colorado from Alchemy Factory Carbon, the frame has a dropped stay design that will clear up to a 700c x 50 or 650b x 2.2″ tire.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193336/Alchemy-argos-titanium-hardtail-geometry.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193336/Alchemy-argos-titanium-hardtail-geometry.png\" alt=\"Alchemy rogue gravel bike\" width=\"918\" height=\"269\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193336/Alchemy-argos-titanium-hardtail-geometry.png 918w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193336/Alchemy-argos-titanium-hardtail-geometry-297x87.png 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193336/Alchemy-argos-titanium-hardtail-geometry-800x234.png 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193336/Alchemy-argos-titanium-hardtail-geometry-120x35.png 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193336/Alchemy-argos-titanium-hardtail-geometry-768x225.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 918px) 100vw, 918px\"></a></p><p>Given the amount of gravel suspension forks we’re seeing, it’s worth pointing out that the Rogue is suspension corrected. The “progressive gravel geometry” includes a 70-71.5º head tube angle depending on the size, and a 73.5º seat tube angle.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191131/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20219.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191131/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20219.jpg\" alt=\"Alchemy rogue dropper post\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191131/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20219.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191131/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20219-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191131/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20219-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191131/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20219-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191131/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20219-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Obviously, the frame is compatible with wireless droppers, but Alchemy states the frame is also compatible with hydraulic droppers as well. We’ll get more details on all the mounts, but it appears that there are three water bottle mounts, a top tube mount, and a rear rack mount on the inside of the seat stays.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191124/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20216.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191124/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20216.jpg\" alt=\"Alchemy Rogue\" width=\"1200\" height=\"664\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191124/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20216.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191124/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20216-297x164.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191124/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20216-800x443.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191124/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20216-120x66.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191124/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20216-768x425.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191113/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20211.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191113/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20211.jpg\" alt=\"Alchemy Rogue red\" width=\"1200\" height=\"664\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191113/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20211.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191113/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20211-297x164.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191113/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20211-800x443.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191113/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20211-120x66.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191113/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20211-768x425.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191120/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20214.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191120/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20214.jpg\" alt=\"Alchemy Rogue \" width=\"1200\" height=\"664\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191120/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20214.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191120/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20214-297x164.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191120/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20214-800x443.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191120/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20214-120x66.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191120/Alchemy-Rogue-gravel-bike-sea-otter-20214-768x425.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Like the rest of Alchemy’s lineup, there are custom paint and finish options available with pricing starting at <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=bc9bec8a-e945-427c-be5d-909db8f98199&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Falchemybikes.com%2Fproducts%2Frogue-gravel-bike\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">$4,299</a> for the frameset module and builds from <a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=bc9bec8a-e945-427c-be5d-909db8f98199&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Falchemybikes.com%2Fproducts%2Frogue-gravel-bike\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">$7,999-$9,999</a>. Alchemy is accepting reservations now with deliveries expected for November.</p><h2>Arktos Full Suspension Update</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191111/Alchemy-Arktos-2022-updates2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191111/Alchemy-Arktos-2022-updates2.jpg\" alt=\"Alchemy Arktos flip chip\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191111/Alchemy-Arktos-2022-updates2.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191111/Alchemy-Arktos-2022-updates2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191111/Alchemy-Arktos-2022-updates2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191111/Alchemy-Arktos-2022-updates2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06191111/Alchemy-Arktos-2022-updates2-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>It’s not just new bikes from Alchemy either. Their popular Arktos full suspension mountain bike is getting an update in the form of a new suspension flip chip. The chip serves two purposes – it allows the rider to adjust the geometry between High and Low settings, and allows for a mixed wheel ‘MX’ setting in the High position.</p><p>The Flip Chip will be available on the Arktos 120, 135, and 150 complete bikes plus the new Arktos 135 &amp; 150 MX builds with a 29″ front and 27.5″rear wheel.</p><div id=\"attachment_273865\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193340/Alchemy-Arktos-120-geometry-flip-chip.png\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273865\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193340/Alchemy-Arktos-120-geometry-flip-chip.png\" alt=\"Alchemy Arktos 120\" width=\"500\" height=\"276\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193340/Alchemy-Arktos-120-geometry-flip-chip.png 500w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193340/Alchemy-Arktos-120-geometry-flip-chip-297x164.png 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193340/Alchemy-Arktos-120-geometry-flip-chip-120x66.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273865\">Arktos 120 Geometry</p></div><div id=\"attachment_273866\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193343/Alchemy-Arktos-135-geometry-flip-chip.png\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273866\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193343/Alchemy-Arktos-135-geometry-flip-chip.png\" alt=\"Alchemy Arktos 135 geometry\" width=\"558\" height=\"220\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193343/Alchemy-Arktos-135-geometry-flip-chip.png 558w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193343/Alchemy-Arktos-135-geometry-flip-chip-297x117.png 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193343/Alchemy-Arktos-135-geometry-flip-chip-120x47.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273866\">Arktos 135 Geometry</p></div><div id=\"attachment_273867\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193345/Alchemy-Arktos-150-geometry-flip-chip.png\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-273867\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193345/Alchemy-Arktos-150-geometry-flip-chip.png\" alt=\"Alchemy Arktos 150 geometry\" width=\"549\" height=\"217\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193345/Alchemy-Arktos-150-geometry-flip-chip.png 549w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193345/Alchemy-Arktos-150-geometry-flip-chip-297x117.png 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/06193345/Alchemy-Arktos-150-geometry-flip-chip-120x47.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 549px) 100vw, 549px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-273867\">Arktos 150 Geometry</p></div><p>For all three suspension travels, flipping the chip to the High setting adds 0.75º to the head tube and sea tube angle.</p><p>Moving forward, complete bikes will be offered with SRAM GX Eagle, and X01 Eagle, Shimano XT, and custom options available by&nbsp;request.&nbsp;Available this halloween, complete bikes will start at $5,499 and will range up to $7,499.</p><h2>In-house Cerakote plus new paint?</h2><p>Want a more durable bike finish that’s also lighter than paint? Sounds crazy, right? But that’s what Alchemy says is possible with their new in-house Cerakote finishes. Cerakote is the name brand of a thin-film ceramic coating that is more durable than liquid paint and about 1/6th of the thickness making it lighter. The result is a light weight finish that will stand the test of time, and one that is available in multiple colors. Along with the Cerakote, Alchemy is offering a new prismatic harlequin finish in addition to their custom paint options.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=el&amp;merchant_id=bc9bec8a-e945-427c-be5d-909db8f98199&amp;website_id=3407ca35-0b50-44fe-aeb1-9ab6a93bba54&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Falchemybikes.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>alchemybikes.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"2b9dfc865034325e5277620832e2a5434b03c947f5524daf03f571cda5cc598d","category":"Cycling"}